>ne is under the dash and is fine. Where is the 
>other? How does the wire make it to the sender? Is the sender grounded 
>where it is, or does a ground wire snake out of the gas tank region somewhere?

It's in the gastank. If you follow the wire into the body below the gastank you can pull the grommet and then pull enough of the wire though and disconnect the sender from the 2-way tee. Then you can retest it and determine if it's truly the wire or the sender.

